<TITLE> Blast at Rajshahi Poly injures 4 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rajshahi, Jan 3 (bdnews24.com)  A blast at Rajshahi Polytechnic Institute on Sunday injured at least four students, police said. Boalia police chief Jasim Uddin said the explosion occurred at around 3:30pm at Room 202 of Shah Neyamatullah Hall. Jasim said it looked like the blast occurred as the students were trying to hide the explosives. Police recovered evidence and investigation is underway, he added. Several witnesses also said the blast occurred while some students were trying to make a cocktail bomb. At least one of the injured students, identified as 'Matin' of the civil engineering department, was severely hurt and admitted to Rajshahi Medical College Hospital, said police. Another of the injured students 'Firoz', also of the civil engineering department, claimed that "Chhatra Shibir activists threw a bomb from outside". Students of rival groups brought out angry demonstrations on campus following the incident. Additional police were deployed, the police chief said. bdne
